                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2969: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-10T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 10, 1918—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 12—12:40
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33 [<hi rend="italic">3?</hi>]. Reports have reached me from French, English,
                    Greek and American Red Cross sources that Bulgarian officials are rendering
                    repatriation of Greeks as difficult as possible and subject them to great and
                    unnecessary hardships making them pay railroad fare and other expenses. Another
                    report less well confirmed as coming only from Greek sources is that Bulgarians
                    in emigrating eastern Macedonia are taking with them all horses, cattle, flocks,
                    et cetera, which is in distinct violation of terms of armistice. French
                    commander in chief whom I saw in Salonica and who is expected here shortly told
                    me that he intends to speak energetically to the Bulgarian Government regarding
                    these two points. Above repeated to Paris.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
